1、2024年将会是人形机器人量产前夜，为了找到合适的应用场景，在既定的场景下尽快完成调试，人形机器人将密集参与产业互动，从而为真正量产做好准备。

2024 will be the eve（） of mass production（） for humanoid robots（）.
In order to find suitable application scenarios and complete debugging as quickly as possible within predetermined（） settings,
humanoid robots will intensively（） participate in industrial interactions, thus preparing for true mass production.

2、Figure AI 的仿人设计与 OpenAI 的人工智能技术之间的这一开创性融合的核心是具身智能。
具身智能超越了传统的人工智能，它将智能集成到机器人等物理实体中，使它们能够感知、学习和动态地与环境互动。

At the heart of this groundbreaking（） integration between Figure AI's humanoid design
and OpenAI's artificial intelligence technology is embodied intelligence（）.

Embodied intelligence transcends（） traditional AI by integrating intelligence into physical entities like robots,
enabling them to perceive, learn, and dynamically interact with（） their environment.

3、中国目前占全球具身智能供应链的 38%，而美国、欧洲和日本分别占 26%、24%和 12%。
粤港澳大湾区占全中国具身智能供应链的55%以上，粤港澳大湾区已发展成为全球具身智能供应链的中心，
不仅拥有成熟的供应链，而且拥有全球技术巨头来推动先进人工智能技术的发展。

China currently accounts for 38% of the global supply chain for embodied intelligence,
while the United States, Europe, and Japan account for 26%, 24%, and 12% respectively.

The Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area accounts for more than 55% of China's embodied intelligence supply chain.
The Greater Bay Area has developed into a global center for the embodied intelligence supply chain,
not only possessing a mature supply chain but also hosting global tech giants
to drive the development of advanced artificial intelligence technology.
